news.title: Mysuru development body mulling over building vertical housing structures
news.para: Rajeev said, “It is not easy to distribute sites at these prices. Muda has accepted this fact, and is considering other options. Vertical housing structures seems like a viable solution for Mysuru city.”

news.title: Distribution of free e-patta starts in Tamil Nadu, 3.35 lakh people to benefit
news.para: In the past, the state government had extended free house site patta to thousands of people on lands taken over by the revenue, Adi Dravida and Tribal Welfare, BC and MBC and minorities welfare departments from individuals and unobjectionable government poramboke lands.

news.title: Builders in Hyderabad observe one-day strike over costs
news.para: Telangana Developers Association (TDA) president GV Rao demanded that the government remove import duty of 7.5% on steel and reduce GST on steel and other building materials.

news.title: Panel for structural audit of buildings gets Noida Board nod
news.para: The Board also approved the formation of a high-level committee of officials drawn from the three development authorities in GB Nagar for chalking out a framework for the structural audit of highrises, a move that comes in the wake of the Chintels Paradiso collapse in Gurgaon.

news.title: Bank consortium gives final approval of Rs 1,500 crore for Amrapali projects: SC
news.para: ​A bench of Justices UU Lalit and Bela M Trivedi was told by court receiver R Venkataramani that the rest of the amount could not be released as banks said that for the purposes of disbursal of funds they would require equitable mortgage by deposit of title deeds as a pre-condition.

news.title: Noida authority's relaxations to help realtors get stress funds
news.para: The Noida Authority has decided to grant mortgage permission reschedule payment of dues for next two years to any developer that qualifies for the Special Window for Affordable and Mid-Income Housing (SWAMIH) fund.

news.title: Maharashtra govt to initiate disciplinary action on 44 officers for violation of RERA
news.para: The state had appointed a four-member squad for checking such documents from all sub-registrar offices in 2020 and a detailed report was submitted last year. The order was issued based on this report, state IGR Shravan Hardikar said on Monday.

news.title: Supertech's twin tower homebuyers' interest will be protected, says SC
news.para: Realty firm Supertech Ltd informed the top court that it will be filing an appeal against the order of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) declaring it bankrupt on a plea filed by the Union Bank of India for non-payment of around Rs 432 crore worth of dues.

news.title: GST hike comes like a ton of bricks on kiln owners
news.para: The kiln owners are up in arms against the Centre, saying the changes were made without any intimation, but tax experts say these were decided in the GST council meeting held in September last year.

news.title: Greater Noida development body plans to rid city of C&D waste by April
news.para: The city’s first C&D waste plant, which is being constructed on 4.5 acres in Ecotech 3, is set to be ready for use in the next 18 months and will be used to recycle waste to make tiles, bricks, slabs and other materials, officials said

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation's records 339% increase in regularization fee in FY22
news.para: The figures for the past four fiscals show that collection of regularisation fee rose steadily save for the pandemic-affected 2020-21 when it went below Rs 1 crore and recorded Rs 68 lakh.

news.title: Pune civic body extends deadline for Gunthewari proposal till June 30
news.para: “All valid proposals which can be regularised under this scheme will be entertained. Additional time has been given so that more and more citizens can benefit from this scheme,” said Vikram Kumar, administrator, PMC.

news.title: Cidco launches mega scheme for plots, shops in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Under the scheme, tenements of various housing projects for MIG and HIG, commercial shops, and plots for residential, commercial, and social purposes, will be made available for sale.

news.title: New Delhi Municipal Council collects Rs 942.3 crore from property tax in FY22
news.para: It claimed that it has achieved the highest ever collection of property tax and said it has maintained a continuous streak for the last few years as a financially well governed municipal organisation.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir looks to complete 54,000 houses under PMAY-G in 2022-23
news.para: ​​It is also planning to provide internet connectivity to all gram panchayats, besides constructing or renovating 700 panchayat ghars across the Union territory during the current financial year, he said.
